cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on online learning of robot manipulation tasks, and the experiments are conducted with the Baxter robot. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a scalable online sequence clustering algorithm based on non-parametric Bayesian mixture models. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a task-parameterized formulation of the approach that autonomously adapts the model to changing environmental situations during manipulation. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses probabilistic principal component analyzers (PPCA) to group new datapoints in their low dimensional subspace. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper uses a hidden semi-Markov model (HSMM) to capture state transition and state duration information online.
